Phillip Schutte and Pieter Doorewaard have been found guilty of culpable homicide in the North West High Court in Mahikeng, on Wednesday following the death of 15-year-old Mathlomola Mosweu in Coligny on 20 April 2017. The duo maintained their innocence, saying the teenager had jumped off their bakkie on their way to the police station, after apprehending him for having allegedly stolen sunflowers. Consequently dubbed the Sunflower Case, the trial commenced in March 2018. For more on the story watch below: 